5:
This is the WORST! I mean, I know
from their point of view I'm
TECHNICALLY the bad guy here, but...
7:
I actually didn't do anything wrong
this time! GRRR!
13:
Someone's vouched for you. 
You're free to go.
17:
Waaah, thank you so much,
everyone!
21:
Uh, mind giving us a rundown on
what happened? We got called here
pretty suddenly, and they skimped
on the details.
31:
Allow me to explain... Because of
that knife of hers, Denah was
accused of illegal trafficking of
prohibited items.
34:
The whole thing was brought to our
attention because someone
actually went and STOLE said knife.
36:
When the perpetrator unsheathed
the knife, he instantly collapsed. 
He still hasn't woken up.
41:
Good riddance! That's a little thing
called KARMA—courtesy of my Lord!
44:
The man is a criminal, yes, but that's
not what got you in hot water—the
knife is. Guild policy strictly prohibits
the use and distribution of cursed
items of its like…
54:
I-I'm being FRAMED here, can't you
see?! I'm innocent!
58:
At long last, freedom! I can finally
breathe the open air and roam the
vast earth! No more must I endure
the TORTURE of being in a prison cell!
66:
Something caught your eye over
there?
71:
Huh... I just... 
You know what, never mind!
75:
So the rumors were true. 
The knife she carries truly is—
78:
MUAHAHA. 
From out the shadows I appear!
81:
Bow before me, insolent fools, for I
am none other than Denah Selphis,
maiden and servant of the KING OF
VOID AND DARKNESS himself!
84:
Gah... How did you know where to
find us?!
86:
HAH. My Lord's power is
immeasurable, transcending even
space and time itself. His ABYSSAL
EYE led me here!
89:
However, I suppose we might have
something in common as well. I take
it you are also loyal servants of my
Lord?
91:
But if you are attempting to curry
favor with him, I have to disappoint
you. Before you stands his MOST
TRUSTED confidant, the one and only—
94:
Quiet! And here I thought you might
be different, but no—you are an
utterly ordinary fool.
96:
Can you even begin to understand
the dangerous powers you're
playing with here?!
97:
They are not something for
commonfolk like you to meddle with.
We may still make it in time for the
ceremony—hand over the knife to
us.
107:
ORDINARY?! Far from it! It's YOU who
are nothing but ordinary, weak,
powerless humans! How dare you
speak like that to ME?!
109:
You stand zero chance of besting
me—not with the powers at my
disposal!
116:
HAHAHA.... So weak, so frail... 
You humans break so easily!
118:
Wh-what the hell are you?! 
No… Could it be—
126:
HEAR ME, feeble humans. You who
are still bound to the shackles of
your mortality!
128:
The time has come for mankind to
leave its infancy behind and—
131: There she is. Denah is over here.
136: Denah! We've been looking for you!
142:
Oh. Alk! And Stella? What are you
doing here?!
145:
You suddenly disappeared! We were
worried about you.
147:
Given how terrible you are with
directions, we were worried you
might have ended up in the
Farlands or something!
153:
I'm sorry to make you all worry like
that!
158:
What were you doing in a place like
this?
166:
Oh, um. Yeah, I guess I had a bit of a
scuffle. But to be fair, they were
some REAL meanies.
170:
"Meanies," huh? I hope that's not all 
it takes for you to start a fight with
someone...
174:
I-it's not! What am I supposed to do
with such insolent fools who are
deaf to the PHANTOM CALL—
177:
Phantom what? I can't keep all your
void magic lingo straight. You need
to make me a list or something.
181:
It's fine! It doesn't matter anyway. 
I don't even remember what I was
doing to begin with!
185:
More importantly than that—
I'm hungry!
What's for dinner today, Alk?
188:
Dinner? I was planning on making
curry today.
192:
Alk's curry is very delicious. Even
when he makes it with no
ingredients.
196:
N-no ingredients? Who eats PLAIN
curry? Alk, are you poor or
something?!
199:
H-hey! I'm doing just fine financially,
thank you very much. And don't
worry—we've got stuff to put in the
curry today.
202:
Awesome! Let's go, then!
Onward, to Starview Village!
